{{- /* 
============================================================================
Dotenv Environment Variables Template
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
This template generates a .env file (dotenv format) commonly used by many
applications and frameworks. It creates KEY=VALUE pairs that can be loaded
as environment variables.

Usage:
  - Include this file in your project root or load it with dotenv libraries
  - Variables are automatically available as environment variables
  - The template expects data with: { Items: map[string]string }
  - Example output creates .env file for local development

Security:
  - .env files typically contain sensitive data
  - Add .env to .gitignore to prevent committing secrets
  - Use different .env files for different environments
  - Do NOT commit generated files with real secrets to version control

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Template logic:
  - Iterates over .Items map, creating KEY=VALUE pairs
  - Uses standard dotenv format (KEY="value")
============================================================================
*/ -}}
{{range $key, $value := .Items -}}
{{$key}}="{{$value}}"
{{end -}}
